== 禁忌 ==
{{main|{{le|关于西瓜的刻板印象|Watermelon stereotype}}}}
西瓜在[[美国|美国]]被視為[[種族歧視|種族歧視]]黑人的象徵符號，盖因大众误认为黑人极其爱吃西瓜故。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/2218572 |title=入隊小禮送「西瓜」 美國消防員竟為此丟了工作 |work=自由時報電子報 |date=2017-10-10 |accessdate=2017-10-11 |archive-date=2021-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210512185331/https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/2218572 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Cambridge 1">{{cite web |url=http://www.cambridge.org/us/books/kiple/cucumbers.htm |title=II.C.6. – Cucumbers, Melons, and Watermelons |publisher=The Cambridge World History of Food |accessdate=March 31, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130601170952/http://www.cambridge.org/us/books/kiple/cucumbers.htm |archivedate=2013年6月1日 |df= }}</ref><ref name="Atlantic">William Black. "[https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2014/12/how-watermelons-became-a-racist-trope/383529/ How Watermelons Became a Racist Trope] {{Wayback|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2014/12/how-watermelons-became-a-racist-trope/383529/ |date=20210512185349 }}", ''[[The_Atlantic|The Atlantic]]'', 8 December 2014. Retrieved 20 August 2016</ref>

